Pregnancy

Krisztian Papp

18 December 2019

1 Data

1.1 Gene list

l <- read_excel("data/gene_ranking.xlsx", sheet="raw")
names(l)[7] <- "abs_ww_abs_coef"
l

1.2 Annotation

The HUGO page (https://www.genenames.org/download/custom/) was used to download a table that contains the gene IDs (table downloaded on 18.11.2019).

hgnc <- read_tsv(file="data/genenames_20191120.txt", col_names = c("HGNC_ID", "Approved_symbol", "Approved_name", "Status", "Previous_symbols", "Synonyms", "Accession_number", "RefSeq_ID", "NCBI_Gene_ID_by_NCBI", "Ensembl", "Date_approved", "Date_modified", "Date_symbol_changed", "NCBI_Gene_ID", "Ensembl_by_ensembl" ), skip = 1) 
hgnc <- dplyr::select( hgnc, Approved_symbol, NCBI_Gene_ID ) %>%
     drop_na()

2 Analysis

plot(l$abs_ww_abs_coef)
abline(h=0.08)

  • Graph above shows the abs_ww_abs_coef values.

Only those genes were inlcuded the analysis, where abs_ww_abs_coef>0.08 (this is true for 192 genes):

l <- l[l$abs_ww_abs_coef>0.08,]
l

3 Over Representation Analysis

  • https://yulab-smu.github.io/clusterProfiler-book/chapter2.html#over-representation-analysis

3.1 KEGG database

l_symbol <- merge(l, hgnc, by.x="gene", by.y="NCBI_Gene_ID") %>%
     dplyr::select( Approved_symbol, gene, abs_ww_abs_coef )%>%
     arrange(desc(abs_ww_abs_coef))
genelist <- as.character(l_symbol$Approved_symbol)
h<- read.gmt("data/c2.cp.kegg.v7.0.symbols.gmt")
egmt <- enricher(genelist, TERM2GENE=h)
head(egmt, n=100L)
  • Link to KEGG_GLUTATHIONE_METABOLISM patway http://software.broadinstitute.org/gsea/msigdb/cards/KEGG_GLUTATHIONE_METABOLISM

3.2 Gene Ontology Analysis

3.2.1 Full GO database

genelist <- l$gene
ego <- enrichGO(gene          = genelist,
                OrgDb         = org.Hs.eg.db,
                #ont           = "CC",
                pAdjustMethod = "BH",
                pvalueCutoff  = 0.01,
                qvalueCutoff  = 0.05, 
                readable = TRUE)
head(as.data.frame(ego@result))
  • The same genes (MGST1/GSTP1/GSTM4) are in the first two significant pathways (glutathione binding, oligopeptide binding)

3.2.2 Only Cellular Component

http://geneontology.org/docs/ontology-documentation/

genelist <- l$gene
ego <- enrichGO(gene          = genelist,
                OrgDb         = org.Hs.eg.db,
                ont           = "CC",
                pAdjustMethod = "BH",
                pvalueCutoff  = 0.01,
                qvalueCutoff  = 0.05, 
                readable = TRUE)
head(as.data.frame(ego@result))
  • Only the first three hits are significant
